inn1.comm: he lets it go on bounce alone! Irfan pitches on a length from over the wicket, on a middle stump line, Guptill shoulders arms and the ball flies over the top of middle stump
driven to mid-off this time
played from the crease towards extra cover, Guptill was looking to drive that on the on side but got squared up a touch
cut in half, sheer pace from Irfan, good length and seaming in a touch after angling across the right-hander, Guptill was late on the shot
width outside off and Guptill gets going with a firm cut off the back foot through covers
short of a length and wide outside off, Guptill shoulders arms
begins with a wide one outside leg stump, slanting past Latham
tries to flick the ball with the angle into him off the pads but misses and is hit on the pad
another really wide ball down leg side
a full length on off and middle, Latham moves forward and punches towards mid off
good length and straight, about 138 kph, Latham gets forward and defends with a straight bat
turned off the pads with the angle into him in front of square leg for a single
a full length but the line is too wide outside off to entice the right-hander
slightly closer to off stump this time but still wide enough for Guptill to let it go through to the keeper
rides the bounce and plays the ball off his body towards square leg
good length outside off, Latham gets forward and shoulders arms watchfully
a length ball rises into Latham's hips, he stays in his crease and tucks the ball towards square leg
shot, the length is full this time from Irfan, outside off stump. Latham moves forward and drives with a lot of punch, hitting the gap between mid off and extra cover
turned off the pads behind square for a single
short of a length, pitching around off and moving away from Guptill, who stays back and shoulders arms
a length ball on off and middle, Latham stays in his crease and plays to square leg
dug in short this time outside off, 138 kph, the ball springs over Latham's head and he doesn't even duck to let it go
bowls a really full one on the pads now and Latham flicks it past square leg
pushed off the front foot into the off side
dabs a length ball behind point off the back foot and sets off for a single
defended from the crease towards the bowler
141 kph, Guptill moves forward and mis-times a drive to cover
gets beside the line of a good length ball round off and plays it towards point
good length pitching on leg and slanting across Guptill, who stays back and defends on the off side

there he goes! The first ODI six at the Basin in nearly ten years would have cleared the ground had the big screen not been in the way! Guptill moves towards the leg side and launches a length ball over long off, driving through the line with a clean swing of the arms. There's a dent on the top of the Don Neely scoreboard now.
defended on the off side
short of a length just outside off, Guptill stands in his crease and drives off the back foot to cover

caught at long leg! The bouncer rises quickly on Guptill, who pulls but top edges it. The ball swirls high in the air towards long leg, where Wahab Riaz runs forward and to his left to judge the catch superbly. It was a lot like the chance Rahat Ali famously dropped off Wahab himself in the World Cup quarterfinal, giving Shane Watson a reprieve.
a fuller ball on the pads, clipped through midwicket for two

An appeal for caught behind is turned down and Pakistan are going to review the not out decision. Amir sent down another sharp bouncer that rose rapidly on Latham, who was trying to hook from his crease. There is no conclusive deviation, though it looks like one. Hot Spot doesn't show anything as the ball whizzes past the glove. There is a blip on the real time snicko though. Pakistan were super confident of their appeal. The third umpire decides that the spike on real time snicko is enough to overturn the decision. Latham has to go.
142 kph! Good length, pitching outside off and angling in towards the stumps, Nicholls strides forward and lets it go! That's a brave leave, well judged in the end
gets behind the line of a straighter delivery and defends from the crease
defended from the crease on the off side, the Pakistan fielders are really vocal in the field, lots of encouragement for Amir
another bouncer, Nicholls ducks under this one
Williamson gets going first ball, dabbing a length ball into the covers for one
good length coming into Nicholls from over the wicket, he stays back and plays towards point
shot! The ball rises from short of a length but Nicolls was ready, swivelling across his crease and rolling his wrists as he pulls through square leg for his first boundary
a sharper short ball outside off this time from Irfan, asking Nicholls to do it again ... he lets it go this time
defended off the back foot on the off side
a full ball on the pads and Nicholls puts it away with a neat push through midwicket, the timing is really good so early in his innings
Williamson defends the ball softly towards mid-on, sees the fielder is a bit deep and calls Nicholls through for a single
good length outside off, Nicholls pushes forward and plays the ball towards cover point
good length outside off, was that a bit slower? Might have been because it bounced a second time before reaching the keeper. Nicholls let it go
good length outside off at 140 kph, defended towards point from the crease
jumps back and dabs a short of a length ball towards third man
jumps back and across and plays a short of a length ball down on the leg side
a length ball but the line is a bit too straight, Nicholls stays in his crease and tucks the ball off his hips behind square
good length just outside off, Williamson stays back and punches behind point
a fuller ball outside off, Nicholls moves forward - he isn't simply hanging back because of Irfan's height - and punches through extra cover
shot! Williamson jumps back to one that rises from short of a length, he has both feet off the ground as he drives through cover, head was so balanced as he made contact
Irfan goes around the wicket and angles a good length ball into the right hander, Williamson jumps back and defends
a fuller length just time outside off, defended from the crease on the off side
that's a poor ball to start with, a half volley slanting across the left-hander at 126kph, Nicholls meets it on the front foot and drives to the cover boundary

edged and dropped! Hafeez has dropped a fairly simple catch! Nicholls flashed away from his body at one that slanted away from a good length with decent bounce. The edge flew quickly but straight to Hafeez at head height. Was on the grass moments later.
defended on the off side
good length angling across the left-hander, Nicholls lets it go
moves back and across and works the ball off his hips to square leg
a fuller ball angling across Nicholls, who refrains from playing away from his body after that edge
132 kph to start with, good length, pitching in line with the stumps and slanting across Williamson, who stays in his crease and punches to cover
moves back and across to the off side and defends towards point
a fuller ball outside off, Williamson stays in his crease and is so steady as he punches through covers
defended off the back foot towards the bowler
good length around off stump, Nicholls stays in his crease and defends on the off side
139 kph, the bouncer just outside off is too high
nudged gently towards mid-on, Irfan is not the swiftest fielder so they take a single
a fuller length around off, driven off the front foot to mid off
short of a length outside off at 131 kph, Nicholls is not flashing at these anymore, lesson learnt apparently
good length angling across the left-hander, Nicholls moves towards the off and dabs the ball towards square leg
a fuller ball on the pads, Williamson aims to flick but does not make contact
tries to pull a short ball but played too early and was beaten as the delivery slanted across him
that short ball is a bit too far outside off, Nicholls shaped to pull but then aborted his shot. Pakistan are not happy with the decision. It was 50-50 I think
a slower ball outside off, driven through covers for a single
short of a length angling into the body, dabbed down close on the leg side for a single
139 kph, good length pitching outside leg and finishing just outside off, Williamson jumps back and defends on the leg side
stays back and squirts a length ball angling across him past the fielder at point
good length outside off, Nicholls stays back and defends on the off side
moves towards the off side and tries to work a short of a length delivery off his hips, doesn't make proper contact and the ball dribbles to the keeper, that was 143kph
short of a length with width outside off, Nicholls cuts firmly but the fielder at point makes a half-stop
too full with lots of width outside off, Nicholls cashes in on the rare loose ball, leaning into the drive and hitting the gap at extra cover
defended off the back foot on the leg side, the bowler runs to his left and fields
gets on the front foot and hits the ball with the angle across him to point
short ball, Nicholls moves towards the off and pulls the ball down through midwicket
short of a length slanting across the left-hander, Nicholls stays back and cuts through point
good length on off and middle, defended towards mid-on and they steal a single before the fielder can move towards the ball to prevent it
tries to pull one that rises from a length and slants across him, ends up mis-timing the ball through midwicket
143 kph, that short of a length ball was on to Nicholls really quickly, he stayed back and swished outside off, sending the ball over first slip off the edge
good length outside off, Nicholls stays back and defend son the off side
the short ball, rises fast on Nicholls who moves across to try and play the ball on the leg side, the delivery was on to him so quickly that he ended up defending awkwardly
a slightly fuller length and the batsman defends from the crease

after a series of fast balls Wahab sent down a slower one, and it was the offcutter I think. The delivery pitched on a fuller length just outside off and angled into the left-hander. Nicholls played from his crease and missed. Wahab appealed confidently for lbw but maybe there was an inside edge on to the pad. I'll need replays to tell. It was too high.
good length outside off and Williamson pokes at it with soft hands, edging the ball but it dies before reaching Hafeez at slip
the short of a length ball does not bounce as much and Nicholls stays back and swats through square leg

bowled him! Williamson has not looked in touch today and he's dragged this one on. The ball pitched on a good length outside off and shaped in just a touch. Williamson drove at it with hard hands and the ball crashed into leg stump off the edge.
good length, pitching outside off and nipping into the right-hander, Elliott tries to defend and gets an inside edge on to the pad

what a ball that is! Anwar Ali has bowled a ripper. It pitched on a fuller length outside off, drawing Elliott into the front foot drive through the off side. The ball moved in late and quite sharply, beating the inside edge this time and hitting the stumps full on
pitches outside off on a good length and slants away from the left-hander, Anderson lets it go
width outside off and Nicholls stays back and cuts behind point
the bouncer, but it is too high and that's a wide
banged in short outside off, the batsman sways out of the way
short of a length again but the line is down leg side this time, Wahab is steaming into the wind, serious effort balls
138 kph, short of a length with bounce outside off, Anderson shoulders arms
short of a length and at the body, Anderson moves back and across and plays the ball down behind square. There's a fielder at short leg mind you
a fuller ball outside off, pushed off the front foot into the covers
stays back and dabs the short of a length ball behind point, the fielder dives to save runs
short of a length outside off, the batsman lets it go
a length ball on the pads, Anderson misses the glance and gets hit on the thigh, the ball goes behind square
good length just outside off, punched from the crease into the covers
short of a length, Nicholls moves across his crease quite early and pulls the ball down along the ground through midwicket
good length angling across the left-hander, Anderson tries to biff it through the off side but mis-times it to mid off
the short ball angles across the left-hander and Anderson is beaten on the pull, loose shot
good length outside off, Nicholls stays back and cuts towards point, mis-timed it
bottom edges a cut off the back foot again, plays it behind point for a single
137 kph and that bouncer takes off, it wasn't over the batsman's head apparently as Anderson was beaten on the pull but the ball ended up soaring over the leaping Sarfraz for four byes
flicked off the pads through square leg for a single
stays back and punches, he was aiming for around point but got a thick edge wide of first slip for a single
played off the front foot into the covers
width outside off and Nicholls plays it through point off the back foot
good length angling just outside off from over the wicket, played towards point of the back foot
short ball, and Anderson rocks back and pulls, hitting the ball flat and hard, Imad Wasim runs quickly to his right from deep square leg and dives to save the boundary

what sort of a shot is that? Anderson stays back in his crease, gets on his toes, and flat-bat pulls the ball from wide outside off between the bowler and the non-striker for another boundary. Dead straight and all along the ground with a flat bat.
defended from the crease towards point
good length just outside off, played from the crease into the covers
short of a length and pretty straight, worked off the hips towards square leg
143 kph, on a good length just outside off from over the wicket, Anderson stays in his crease and defends

he's slogged at this ball and just managed to biff it over the infield between mid-off and extra cover. Amir bowled a skiddy short of a length ball and Anderson was rushed for time as he tried to pull

caught behind! Amir has his second wicket! He pitched short of a length and the ball bounced a bit more than usual on a tight line outside off. Anderson stayed back and pushed at the delivery with hard hands, trying to punch through cover. The edge flew through comfortably to Sarfraz
a full ball, slanting across the right-hander, pitching outside off and moving away, Ronchi lets it go
shot! But Amir won't mind that with slips in place. Ronchi leans into the half-volley slanting across him and drives smoothly through covers to get off the mark
short of a length at the body, played off the hips behind square
short of a length and pretty straight, Ronchi stays back and defends towards point
short of a length and rising outside off, Ronchi lets it go
that is steep bounce from just short of a length, thankfully for the batsman the line was outside off so Ronchi could let it go
stays in his crease and pushes away at a ball angling across him from a good length, the outside edge goes along the ground to third man
short of a length outside off and more steep bounce from the towering Irfan, Nicholls moved towards the ball to play it and then was half-beaten half pulled his bat inside the line
Ronchi's gone! Amir's got his third! Ronchi stays in his crease and wafts at a good length ball that slants across the right-hander from over the wicket. Sarfraz snaffles another edge
140 kph, good length and fast, angling into the left-hander at a skiddy pace, Santner defends on the front foot
oh my word, that was so, so close to the stumps, and Santner let it go! He let it go on bounce of course and has a wry smile after. That was a terrific ball nipping into the left-hander
this time he pushes forward to defend a full and incoming ball and gets an outside edge that falls short of Sarfraz as he dives forward and to his left
a full and fast ball, flicked off the pads through square leg
good length on off stump, defended on the off side. We've just watched two seriously good overs from Irfan and now Amir.
the yorker nearly, homing into the boot from Irfan's release in the skies, the batsman does well to block it out
and now the bouncer, the batsman ducks under it
a fuller ball again, just outside off, Santner defends on the front foot
well bowled! Short of a length just outside off and holding its line, Santner is beaten as he prods off the back foot
good length outside off, Santner strides forward and shoulders arms
again Irfan aims for the boot, Santner nimbly defends, digging the ball out of the blockhole
strays on to the pads this time with a full ball, Santner flicks through midwicket and he'll get three for that
good length outside off, defended off the back foot behind point

140 kph, good length on a great line outside off, the batsman defends. Loud shouts of encouragement from the fielders and Amir has a smile on his face as he walks back to his mark. Really good to see.
good length and straight, defended on the off side

shot! It was a half-volley and Santner wipes off Amir's smile with a superb straight drive, that was hit hard and it went off Amir's boot on its way to the straight boundary. The bowler winces in some pain
replies with the bouncer and Santner ducks under it

another short ball and this time Santner pulls! He gets a top edge though but the ball falls safely out of Sarfraz's reach as the keeper ran towards the short fine leg region to try and take the catch
good length and straight, defended on the back foot
nudged off the back foot gently through midwicket and they race back for a risky second, direct hit would have had the batsman at the striker's end. Sarfraz did not get to the stumps quickly enough
defended off the back foot on the off side
short of a length outside off, defended on the back foot
good length at the body, pinning Santner in his crease, he stays back and defends on the leg side
short of a length on off and middle, Santner can do little but defend on the back foot
beats Nicholls on the drive with a flat ball outside off
pushed into the covers off the front foot
gets down on one knee and sweeps the ball with the angle into him behind square
gets on the front foot and drives firmly to mid-off
bowled on a good length on off stump, Santner defends on the front foot

Santner reaches for the ball wide outside off and slogs, hitting it off the bottom of the bat and slicing it high over the bowler's head. Babar Azam runs a long way to his right from long on, covering a lot of ground, and dives full length, he got fingers on it but could not hold on. Incredibly tough chance with this wind.
shot! Nicholls welcomes Wahab back into the attack with a crisp punch off the back foot, sending the ball racing to the point boundary
tucked off the hips towards square leg for a quick single
short of a length outside off, Santner jumps back and opens the face, steering the ball to the third man boundary, that was more of an outside edge really
stays back and opens the face again, guiding the ball towards third man, more in control this time
short of a length just outside off, the ball holds its line too and the batsman drops his wrists and sways out of the line
strays down leg side with a short of a length ball, Nicholls swats the ball down to long on
strays down leg side, that's not going to help the over rate
cut off the back foot through point for two more
stays back and plays the flat and straight ball off his pads to midwicket
tucked off the pads through square leg for a single
stays back and dabs the ball through point for another single
punched off the back foot but the fielder at midwicket is in the way
a slower pace outside off, it drifts away from the left-hander and Nicholls is beaten on the cover drive
short of a length outside off, Santner uses the room to steer to third man
good length outside off, Santner lets it go
short of a length and fast outside off, Santner prods this time because it is close to the body and is beaten
jumps back and opens the face to steer the ball behind point
good length around off stump, defended from the crease towards point

the slower ball, Nicholls leans into it and nudges on the off side, and that single brings him his maiden ODI fifty. Nicholls had 49 runs in four innings before this game. Well played, he's held a struggling New Zealand together.
defended on the back foot on the off side
goes back and cuts the ball to deep point
goes back again to a flat and quick ball outside off and cuts through point
on the pads from around the wicket, played to midwicket
played off the back foot to midwicket again. Wasim is bowling flat and quick. No flight or turn.
cut off the back foot through point. That over certainly helped the over-rate.
a slow legbreak on the pads, tucked behind square for a single
good length on a wicket to wicket line, played back to the bowler
really slow on the pads, the batsman has to wait a while before turning it through square leg
fuller ball on leg stump, driven to long on for the third single in the over
defended on the off side on the front foot
moves forward and towards leg to hit the ball through wide mid on
cut off the back foot through point, all seems a bit tepid after that pace battery
lunges on to the front foot, gets down low, and nails the sweep, hitting it hard and along the ground to deep midwicket
played off the back foot through point for another single
played back to the bowler, another flat dart that was from Imad
shot! Santner steps out and drills the drive to the long off boundary to bring up the 50 partnership
defended back to the bowler
swept behind square and New Zealand make it to 150
edged and four! No slip in place. Santner swipes at the googly, aiming for a big drive down the ground, but got a thick outside edge that flew past the keeper and fine of short third man
played back to the bowler in more controlled fashion
strays down leg side, another wide, Pakistan have bowled a lot of them today
dabbed from the crease to short third man
driven off the front foot to Azhar Ali, who moves to his left to field
down on one knee to sweep the ball along the ground through square leg
defended on the front foot into the off side
lofted over the infield at wide mid off, he came forward and drove that inside out
steered towards short third man for a single
pushed to point for one more, easy singles on offer now
another push with an open face through point
this time Santner gets beaten outside off stump as he tries to push on the off side
pulled to deep midwicket
punched off the back foot on the off side
goes back and pulls through midwicket

nudged off the front foot close on the leg side, there's a mix up midwicket the batsmen, the fielder runs to his left from midwicket but fails to pick up cleanly, Santner would have been in big trouble at the striker's end otherwise
pushed off the front foot to mid on
steps out but is not to the pitch of the ball, he stabs at it and gets an inside edge towards square leg
goes back and hits the ball along the ground to long on
gets forward and outside the line of off stump and sweeps, he misses and is hit on the pad
pushed off the front foot to midwicket
driven off the front foot to deep cover
tries to swat off the back foot but does not make proper contact
pushed to long on for a single
pushed on the leg side, midwicket is in place to cut off the single
the reverse sweep! Plays it towards backward point
worked off the pads to midwicket, another dot ball
goes back and cuts the ball from off stump through point
gets down low and sweeps the ball to deep square leg
shot! Santner steps out of his crease and drives so smoothly and so straight, this kid is a real talent.
a fuller ball on the pads turned behind square for a single
short of a length around off, the batsman stays back and defends behind point
good length just outside off, Santner stays back and defends on the off side

caught on the pull! Irfan's short of a length ball rises quickly and cramps the left-hander for room from over the wicket. Santner's pull results in a top edge and Sarfraz runs to his right to catch it around short fine leg.
cut off the back foot through backward point
pushed off the front foot towards point
fires it down leg side, Henry misses the flick, Imad appeals for a caught behind but in vain
flat and short, cut hard off the back foot through point
bowled flat on middle stump, punched off dthe back foot to the bowler
riven back to the bowler firmly, Imad fields to his right
stays back and works the ball off the pads behind square, "ONLY ONE" yells Sarfraz
stays in his crease and whips the ball through square to take a single
too flat and on middle and leg, worked off the back foot past the fielder at midwicket
a full ball outside off, driven towards mid off
short of a length and straight, Nicholls moves back and across and short-arm pulls through square leg
a length ball angling across the right-hander, Henry stays in his crease and defends on the off side
a full and quick ball slanting across the right-hander, Henry tries to drive off the front foot and is beaten
the short ball and straight, Henry gets inside the line by moving to the off side as he pulls but he is beaten
a full ball outside off, driven firmly and the fielder at mid-off dives over the ball and makes a half stop. Irfan is done for the day, he's bowled a hustling spell with good pace and bounce
short of a length outside off, cut off the back foot but can't get it past point
short of a length at the body, Nicholls swivels and short-arm pulls through square leg
Henry can hit them! He's just pulled a short ball powerfully to the midwicket boundary
banged in short, the batsman ducks. That was a predictable response from Wahab!
another short ball, this time Henry gets inside the line and tries to pull, gets beaten near his left shoulder
the slower ball on a fuller length on middle and off, Henry defends solidly on the front foot
Anwar Ali's first ball is a short one on leg stump, Nicholls stays in his crease and swivels to pull that to the backward square leg boundary
punched past the bowler for a single, the fielder at mid-off dives to cut off the shot and ends up deflecting it towards mid on
played from the crease on the off side
played back towards the bowler, Ali dives to his left to field

another short ball, Ali does not have the pace to hurry the batsman, Nicholls pulls powerfully and has almost split the gap before Maqsood dives to his left on the square leg boundary to save the four
hit towards mid off for a single and he will keep the strike
the slower ball but there's width outside off, Nicholls reaches for it and slaps it over the infield at cover

that's hit him! Henry takes off his helmet to see it things are okay. He looks good, thankfully. He tried to pull a sharp short ball and missed. He was squared up as he played that and the ball glanced off the collar bone region of the right shouldera on to the grille of his helmet
another short ball and Henry pulls off the front foot but makes no contact
Wahab is letting rip here, a fiery bouncer and Henry is beaten on the pull again, Sarfraz leaps to collect above his head
the slower ball outside off this time and Henry swipes across the line far too early and is beaten once again
mis-times a slog towards mid on, falls short of the fielder. Just the single off that over and Henry will be glad to get to the non-striker's end for a bit
banged in short from over the wicket outside off, Nicholls tries to pull and drag the ball towards the leg side but misses

dragged it on! After a series of short balls, Ali bowls a full one outside off, and Nicholls attempts the booming drive through the off side. He gets an inside edge on to his stumps. Nicholls walks off to applause from the full house at Basin Reserve. He's made his best score today, and in really tough circumstances.
in the blockhole, McClenaghan digs it out to the bowler, some words exchanged
short ball to follow the yorker, McClenaghan swats it past the bowler, not-timed well and mid off runs to his left to field
the slower short ball and Henry pulls too early and is hit on the upper arm of his right hand
this time the slower bouncer is too high, Henry tried to ramp it but was beaten
finally he's hit one and hit it well! Henry swivels and pulls a short ball down leg side, fine leg is in the circle which makes that a really poor delivery
Wahab steams in and bangs in another bouncer, McClenaghan gets out of the way
short of a length and this time the ball does not rise as much and McClenaghan swivels and pulls, hitting the ball flat and hard, and just far enough to clear the square leg boundary
steps out of his crease and jams his bat down at a good length ball and jabs it on the leg side
that's a huge hit! Henry clears his front foot to a length ball and mows it over cow corner, he's slammed it high and on to the roof and out of the ground!

this time he is not in control but the result is the same! Wahab pounds the middle of the pitch again with a short ball and Henry turns his head away from the line of the ball as he hooks. The top edge soars down to long leg and clears the rope
finally he aborts this predictable short ball barrage and bowls a full one outside off, Henry is beaten. Superb over for New Zealand, 19 runs
more short stuff, this time from the returning Amir, wide outside off though and McClenaghan is beaten on the pull
bowled full and too wide outside off, so many extras Pakistan have conceded today
short of a length outside off, pulled through square leg for a single
shot! Henry can hit the long ball all right. It was a full ball and Henry got on the front foot and hit it straight, maybe he did not time it perfectly but it cleared long off quite easily in the end
the slower ball and Henry is beaten because he swung too early
short ball and Henry pulls through square leg

what has cricket come to? McClenaghan moves towards the off side, gets down low, and scoops the full ball so deftly over the head of short fine leg. He hit that front right in front of his stumps. Dilshan would have been proud of that shot had he played it himself.
played through square leg for a single
the reverse sweep but can't beat backward point
nudged off the pads through square leg and the call is for two immediately, superb running
goes back and hits the ball through midwicket
it's all going New Zealand's way at the moment, Henry slogs across the line and top edges the ball over short third man for another boundary
that's no where near the top edge, it's smack out of the middle. Henry brings up the 50 stand by heaving a short ball high and far over deep midwicket
nope, it's full and slow outside off, McClenaghan slogs and gets a bottom edge into the ground to the keeper
full and straight this time, McClenaghan hits it hard to long on
backs away towards leg and slogs too early at a slower ball, he is beaten outside off
another edge, another four, he clears his front foot and slogs across the line at a short ball, the top edge flies over the keeper and third man has no chance
a full ball nearly in the blockhole outside off, driven to cover for a single
short ball, slightly slower too, Wahab has been stubborn with that tactic today and it has not worked for him. McClenaghan slams the pull far over deep midwicket
a full ball wide outside off stump, Henry reaches for it and chops it into the ground, the ball bounces towards cover
a full toss at thigh height, and what does McClenaghan do? He moves towards the off side, gets down on one knee, and scoops it past the keeper. Pakistan look so rattled in the field.
bowled full and fast outside off stump, McClenaghan backed away outside leg and then found himself too far away from the ball to make contact
steps out to a full toss and lofts it into the gap on the cover boundary! Ali was looking for the yorker and missed his length

oh no, oh no, McClenaghan has been smashed in the face by a short ball after he missed the pull. The ball flew through the gap between the peak of the helmet and the grille and smashed into the region near his eye. The force was so much that the ball rebounded on to the grille off his face. That back padding of the helmet has been dislodged and is lying on the pitch. The crowd cheers as McClenaghan gets off his feet and begins to walk off the ground, there's a small swelling already.
edged and four to finish! Boult backs away towards leg and then slashes at a full ball outside off. the thick edge flies wide of the keeper for four. New Zealand have shredded Pakistan to ribbons.

inn2.comm: good length and on a wicket to wicket line, defended on the back foot
short of a length outside off, the batsman lets it go this time
this time the line is too wide outside off
good length just outside off stump, defended on the off side
good length around off stump, the batsman gets behind the line and blocks
full ball with swing away from the right-hander from wide outside off, Azhar chases it with the big drive and misses
defended from the crease on the off side
a length ball on leg and middle, Shehzad moves back and across to work the ball through square leg
short of a length outside off, Azhar stays back and defends on the off side
nudged off the pads towards midwicket
good length on middle and off, Azhar moves towards the off and plays the ball on the leg side
136 kph, good length on a wicket to wicket line, Azhar stays in his crease, presses forward and pushes on the leg side towards midwicket
played back to the bowler on the front foot, wicket to wicket line
a full ball around off stump, defended from the crease on the off side
the bouncer is too high, second wide of the innings already
too full on the pads, Shehzad flicks it through square leg
full just outside off at 137kph, driven on the front foot to mid off
140 kph, in the channel outside off stump, no real movement laterally, Shehzad lets it go
good length just outside off stump, defended towards the bowler with a straight bat
a length ball outside off, Shehzad plays a punchy drive through the covers, Williamson chases from mid off and reels it in
moves back and across to work the ball off his pads behind square
banged in short, the batsman ducks under the bouncer
a fuller ball outside off, Shehzad drives through cover again, not timed well enough to reach the boundary
short of a length outside off, defended from the crease on the off side
dropped with soft hands close on the off side for a single
that's not that short but he manages to pull the ball through square leg
steps out and cuts a short of a length ball, can't beat the infield though
short of a length on the hips, tucked towards square leg
defended from the crease with a straight bat to the bowler
Azhar decides it's time to cut loose, stepping out to a fuller ball and lofting inside out over the infield at cover, a powerful swing of the bat
moves across his crease and works the ball off his pads through midwicket
pitches on a good length, 133kph, and straightens a touch, Shehzad is squared up as he defends
good length just outside off, defended on the front foot on the off side
down the pitch and quietly defended
the bouncer, right over the left shoulder as Azhar swivels to pull and is beaten
length ball angling across the batsman, defended on the off side
short of a length on the hips, jumps back and tucks the ball through square leg
defended into the off side again, just one run off the over
good length outside off, dabbed off the back foot to point
nudged with soft hands towards midwicket, the non-striker slows a bit to let Elliott pass as the bowler races towards the ball, and then continues running the single, makes it easily
a fuller ball on the pads, flicked through square leg for a single
a length ball on middle stump, flicked off the pads through midwicket for one more
flicked off the pads on the front foot through midwicket again
was looking to steer to third man hut got an inside edge on to the pad
a full ball outside off, tries to force it on the leg side but gets a bottom edge towards midwicket
the bouncer is too high once again, that's a wide
defended on the front foot towards point
shot! Simply picked the length ball off his pads and hoisted it over deep backward square leg with a smooth flick
opens the face and plays towards point
shot! Azhar strides forward to a full ball outside off and drives straight past the bowler, extremely graceful
defended from the crease on the off side
a full ball outside off, some shape away from the right-hander, Azhar drives to cover
this one swings quite a bit away from Azhar, who tries to drive on the off side but gets an inside edge on to the legd
defended from the crease on the off side, Azhar begins to run but gets sent back quickly

he's slogged this straight up in the air and Henry settles under it at mid-on. Azhar planted his foot forward and swung across the line at an offcutter. The bat turned in his hand as he made contact and he ended up slicing it in the air. Azhar's match is over, he's not had a good day after the first hour and a half.
good length outside off, Shehzad stays in his crease, opens the face and steers towards point
a full ball swings away from the right-hander, driven on the up towards mid off, Elliott bowls a wicket maiden!
good length on leg and middle, the batsman tries to play from his crease but misses the line and is hit on the thigh
oh my word! Anderson bowls a full ball that angles across the right-hander just outside off and then comes back in at Hafeez, beating the bat on the inside edge and just missing off stump
this time Anderson bowls with a scrambled seam and slants the ball away from the right-hander from a similar line, Hafeez is good enough to let it go
hits the top of the pad again with a short of a length ball that skids on
worked off the pads to square leg
stays back to a length ball and cuts it to point, consecutive maidens for New Zealand, such a rarity in the modern game
a full ball on the pads, clipped behind square leg for a single
pushed off the pads towards wide mid on for a quick single
pitches on a good length just outside off and seams away, the batsman stays back and opens the face to steer to third man
Hafeez waits for the ball to seam away, playing it late towards cover for a single
a full ball with swing away from Shehzad who stays in his crease, presses forward, and drives to mid off

he's holed out to mid off this time! Elliott has a second wicket and he would not have been bowling so early if not for the injury to McClenaghan. Elliott pitched the ball on a good length outside off and got it to seam away from the right-hander, Shehzad got his foot forward and drove away from his body, the ball made contact with the bottom of his bat and went flat and straight to Williamson
short of a length down the leg side, the pull results in a bit of a top edge behind square, he was hurried for time on that shot
punched off the back foot into the covers
a bit of shape into the right-hander from just outside off, driven off the front foot towards point
left alone outside off stump
driven firmly into the covers, nicely timed but straight to the fielder
short arm pulled through square leg
a full ball angles into the right-hander and then seams away, no one has moved the ball as much as Elliott has today. The batsman lets it go
width outside off and the batsman cuts to deep point
steps out and towards the off side to pull a short ball towards cow corner, along the ground, Nicholls covers a lot of ground from deep midwicket and fields
tucked off the pads through square leg
a length ball but too wide outside off, the batsman began to play at it but checked his shot
the ball seams away from the right-hander but the length is short enough to allow Azam to stay back and swat it through wide mid on
short of a length, pitches on leg and middle and straightens into the right-hander instead of going across, Hafeez defends in a hurry
once again Hafeez is cramped for room by Anderson's shape into the right-hander from over the wicket, he gets an inside edge that rolls near his stumps
a fuller ball outside off, Hafeez pushes forward and plays into the covers
a loud appeal for lbw but that probably pitched outside leg stump, Hafeez tried to flick the ball off his pads but missed, it was hitting the stumps but it had just pitched outside leg
pitches outside leg again and this time Hafeez tucks it off his pads through square leg
played off the back foot towards point
good length outside off, some movement away again, the batsman stays back and defends on the leg side
tight line and length on off stump, Azam stays back and defends
strays on to the pads this time, flicked off the hips through square leg
good length on middle and off, the slow pace and the seam movement away is making it hard to find any timing, defended on the off side
wider outside off stump, left alone this time
moves forward and towards the off side to pull the ball behind square
nudged off the pads off the back foot for a single behind square leg
good length and line around off, defended on the front foot
steps out to flick the full ball through midwicket
worked off the pads towards square leg
driven on the front foot but to the fielder at cover
dragged a bit short so Hafeez goes back and pulls through midwicket
full ball, Hafeez targets the leg side and gets a leading edge that spoons over backward point
sliding into the pads, flicked through backward square leg
short and width outside off, confidently to sweeper cover
floated outside off, Elliott finds the outside edge, which runs down to third man
back of a length, played back to the bowler
veering into the pads again, twirled away.... short midwicket flings to his right and stops the ball
slides on middle, kept out
driven to long-on for one
pushed through, drilled to cover
skids off the surface, driven. The man at short cover dives to his right to stop the ball
tapped past the bowler to mid-off for an urgent single
shorter and outside off, Hafeez skips back, picks up, and skies a pull over midwicket. Henry tracks back from mid-on, dives, but the ball eludes his grasp
nurdled off the pads behind square
dug in short on off, front-foot pull to the midwicket fence with some authority. That's only the second four and third boundary in the innings
back of a length and largely holds its line outside off, leaden-footed stab and a miss
back of a length, chopped towards point
banged in short, tests Hafeez, who flaps a pull to mid-on. They take on Henry who was hanging back in the circle. Quick single
tossed up and drifts in, Azam ventures down the pitch and lifts it over mid-off. He did not middle it, though
short dart on off, firmly pulled towards deep midwicket. Boult, who had initially moved to his right, recovers and sprints belatedly to his left, but can't swat the ball in. The result is four
down the track and lofted to long-off
fizzes off the surface and raps the pad
dropped short and outside off, cut away in the gap at backward point
full ball at off, tapped back to the bowler on the front foot
picked away off the pads to fine leg
bumper, ducked under
width outside off, slower one as Anderson rolls his fingers across it. Hafeez Azam crunches a square-cut and finds the boundary again
clipped off the pads towards the midwicket region
Anderson bangs another lifter, Azam ducks under it again
dug in outside off, controlled pull in front of square
drifts in, tucked around the corner to backward square leg
pushed to cover
straight ball, worked to midwicket
Santner shortens his length outside off, cut through backward point
tossed up, pushed back to the bowler
banged in short, pulled behind square leg
tucked away off the pads for two
103ks slower full ball, bunted to mid-on
Hafeez skips out, the bowler is wary of it as he bangs a bouncer and forces the batsman to hunker down
full on middle and leg, clipped straight to midwicket
dug in short and outside off, Hafeez skips back for a pull. Nicholls moves to his left from deep midwicket and then forward, dives, but looked like the ball died in front of him
short ball on off, fended in front of cover
short again, Hafeez swivels on the back foot and pulls it in the air, behind square, beats the two men in the deep
full on off, turned to midwicket
full on the pads, worked through square leg
full and on the stumps, sweetly driven down the ground
tight line on off, patted to point on the front foot
short and outside off, pulled to long-on
played to point
wide outswinger, past the tramline
extra bounce on this short ball outside off as Hafeez is beaten on the cut
slippery ball on a fourth-stump line, kept out
clears long-on. Pushed full and outside off, Hafeez gets under it and launches it over the leaping fielder
length and outside off, caressed to the off-side sweeper
back of a length ball, dabbed with soft hands, straight to Guptill at backward point for a speedy single. He can't throw the stumps down at the striker's end
Guptill in action at backward point again. He flings to his left to smartly stop this hit
back of a length and outside off, tapped towards point
short, rising ball outside off, Azam miscues a pull in front of midwicket
hurrying ball on off, chopped towards backward point. Guptill swoops down on the ball
half volley on the leg stump, handsomely flicked to the right of midwicket
dangled outside off, nudged to cover
loopier and outside off, carved behind point

KW breaks the stand with his part-time spin. Hafeez can't beat the fielder now, after having struck a six earlier. This was pushed through flatter and quicker as Hafeez danced out. He does not connect well with a lofted hit. Drags it to Henry at long-on
tossed up, pushed towards mid-off
played back to the bowler
Maqsood flits around in the crease and nudges it to square leg
shorter and outside off, cut away. Guptill dives full length and palms it away behind point
length and outside off, eased to cover on the front foot. A fumble allows a single
bouncer on the leg stump, flies to the keeper as the batsman sinks under it
angled in on off, driven to mid-off
corker from Boult. Inswinging yorker, dug out
Azam skips back, swivels, and controls a pull behind square against a short ball
pushed back to the bowler
sliding into the pads, worked to fine leg. The pair hare across for the second. Milne fires an accurate throw. But a full-length dive saves Azam
dropped short, pulled behind square on the leg side
chopped to the covers
eased down the ground for one
flatter and outside off, Maqsood steps away outside leg, creates swinging room. He then skips back at the last moment and punches in the gap at cover
shorter and outside off, flayed to deep cover
rising ball on off, chopped towards point
pitched up outside off, the batsman reaches out and drives it crisply behind point
Boult sprays the slower ball outside off. Knuckle ball? It goes wrong, though
dragged short, pulled to deep midwicket
helped down to third man
Boult bangs a lifter, it sails over the ducking batsman. Wide called
length and slanting away outside off, steered to third man
back of a length and outside off, skids on, beats the outside edge
full and swerves away outside off, finds the outside edge, run away to short third man
Elliott sucks pace off this, nudged off the pads behind square
another slower ball, bunted to the leg side
Azam brings up an impressive fifty with a pulled single to deep square leg. Controlled the shot well against the short ball
fractionally short, sits up outside off, forced to sweeper cover
good length ball on middle, blocked on the front foot
angling away on a fuller length, punchily played to short cover
flicked off the hips through backward square leg
full and slanting away, guided to backward point
short ball on the hips, turned to midwicket
full and on middle and leg, knocked towards midwicket
Elliott strikes again! He tests Maqsood with a bouncer. The batsman fails, taking his eyes off the hook. Top edged to long leg
back of a length and outside off, punched towards backward point
awayswinger outside off, defensive stab and a miss
another awayswinger outside off, patted to backward point
Sarfraz gets on top of this short ball, pulled around the corner for one
floated fuller and slower on middle and leg, milked down to long-on
flat and full, driven to long-on
drifts in on off, nudged in front of midwicket
slides in, defended on the front foot
Azam uses his feet and secures a single to mid-off
Sarfraz stretches forward and sweeps to short fine leg
lobbed up and spins, Sarfraz shapes to drive and gets an inside snick, which rolls to the leg side
leg-side wide
Anderson tucks the batsman up for room. Chopped in front of cover for one
short and width outside off, cut to deep point
leg-stump short ball, pulled to fine leg
dug in short but it does pose much threat. Short at 130ks, smartly pulled through backward square leg with a whirl of the wrists
Anderson replies with some swing and strikes the pad as Azam misses the flick
short and down leg, helped to long leg
full on middle, driven to long-on. Sarfraz looks for two. They settle with one
slides on, Azam uses his feet and pushes it defensively

slides on outside off with extra bounce, Azam skips back and top-edges a cut to short third man. Sarfraz searches for a single, but is sent back. He tumbles, drops his bat on the floor, in the middle of the pitch. Sarfraz then recovers, dives desperately, and makes his ground, despite getting hit by the ball. Along the way, did he change his line, blocking the throw? Guptill and KW get together and have a chat with the umpire. Guptill was quite animated while KW was as cool as ever. Appeal for obstructing the throw? Sarfraz just got up after tumbling, did not disturb the throw... He just fell over to the other side of the pitch and then ran in a dead-straight line
whipped to cow corner
Sarfraz goes low and sweeps a four behind square
flat dart on the leg stump, helped behind square on the leg side
shorter on leg, clipped behind square on leg
shorter and outside off, cut away in front of square
back of a length and outside off, slashed to third man
Azam perishes to the short ball too. He gives it away He sets up for a pull from just outside off but only miscues it down the throat of Nicholls at deep midwicket
diverted off the pads fine on the leg side
width outside off, bottom-edged cut to third man
full and darted on the pads, flicked to midwicket
straight ball on off, blocked back

Wasim has been snaffled down the leg side. Given out by umpire Llong. The bowler was so confident that he gestured for a review, just before the finger went up. Drifting down leg, innocuous ball. There is a tiny nick behind to Ronchi
drifts in,  defended
tossed up, knocked towards midwicket
pitched up on off, pushed to cover on the front foot
back of a length on middle and leg, nudged in front of square for one
lifting ball outside off, beats the flashing cut
dug in outside off, swatted to midwicket
Sarfraz ramps a short ball outside off to third man
back of a length on off, chopped to backward point
back of a length and outside off, late-cut to third man
slides in with the arm and hits the pad
another arm-ball, the batsman targets the leg side, gets a leading edge to cover
slapped from outside off to deep mid-off
looped up on off, laced down the ground
down the pitch and whipped behind square
flighted and full on off, dropped defensively in front of point
short and outside off, Sarfraz rides it to third man
full and outside off, dabbed with soft hands to third man
the batsman skips out, the short ball gets big on him and cramps him. Swatted to midwicket
bouncer, banged in outside off. Swing and a miss
another lifter, this is down leg, flies through to Ronchi. Wide
short on off, Anwar hops and secures a single towards square leg
back of a length on middle, pushed to cover
Yes, Anwar Ali can bat. Shortish and outside off, he flits around in the crease and slugs it flat over long-on
short on leg, following Anwar, who was looking to make room. Dabbed towards point
back of a length, tapped to cover
Boult hurls a bouncer outside off. Anwar hooks and only connects with thin air
Anwar feigns away, Boult hits a fuller length on middle, chipped over the bowler's head
bouncer down leg, wide
banged in, fended in front of cover
Sarfraz makes room and slaps a slower one to deep point
short on off, helped to third man
Sarfraz steps away outside leg, the bowler follows him with a short ball. Hooked over midwicket
Sarfraz manufactures room again and gets a short ball. This is ramped away past the diving third man fielder
back of a length, Sarfraz backs away and cuts through point
back of a length slower ball outside off, Sarfraz, having made room again, cuts to third man

Sarfraz holes out to Corey Anderson, running to his left from deep midwicket. Well-judged take. Full and on middle, Sarfraz swings but does not get enough power behind that hit. Pakistan seven down and sinking
Wahab is greeted by a lifting ball, fended to third man
fractionally short and outside off, Anwar Ali slogs hard and finds Latham at midwicket. The fielder did not even have to budge. Two wickets in three balls for Boult
bouncer, ducked under
length ball around off, sliced to point
short and angled in from round the stumps, played to point
back of a length, angled in, and climbs over the stumps. Wahab goes for a big whoosh and does not connect
lifter outside off, Wahab sways his upper body out of the way
another swing and a miss to a short ball
short ball again, Wahab sizes it up, flat-bats it, forcing his partner to duck for cover. Tennis-swung away for four
another short ball outside off, swish and a miss
lifting ball outside off, Amir can't ramp it away
full on the stumps, pushed to cover

knocked'em over. Boult has a big smile. The middle stump is knocked back. Boult hunts for a yorker and bowls a full toss, which is good enough. Amir makes room and drags it back onto the stumps. The zing bails go flying
Boult nails a yorker just a shade outside, dips under the bat
length ball on middle, defended
Boult wraps up a 70-run win. Pinpoint yorker, this (reverse-)swings away as well, beating the poke of Irfan to crash into the off stump
